# Luke's secrets — the plaintext TEMPLATE. Copy to `secrets.env`, fill it in
# ON THE BOX, then encrypt it with SOPS into `secrets.enc.env` (which IS
# committed, safely, because it's ciphertext). See SECRETS.md.
#
#   cp .env.example secrets.env         # fill in on the box, never commit
#   sops --input-type dotenv --output-type dotenv -e secrets.env > secrets.enc.env
#   git add secrets.enc.env             # the encrypted file is safe to commit
#   shred -u secrets.env                # destroy the plaintext
#
# NEVER commit secrets.env or .env — only the SOPS-encrypted secrets.enc.env.

# --- Luke's own identity ------------------------------------------------
# Luke's nostr key (nsec1… or 64-hex). His npub is his public identity and
# what your grant points at. GENERATE ON THE BOX, never in chat.
LUKE_NSEC=

# --- Nave's identity — the project voice -------------------------------
# Nave's OWN nsec, a role key. Luke drafts posts as Nave; you approve each
# one via Telegram; this key signs them. GENERATE ON THE BOX. This is a
# role key, custodial by design — it is NOT your sovereign (jaf@) key.
NAVE_NSEC=

# --- The master: your SOVEREIGN identity, the ONE key the gate lets in --
# Your npub (public, not secret). Your real handle is jaf@dequalsf.com; its
# NIP-05 is published on dequalsf.com and its nsec NEVER lives on this box.
# The gate opens only for a NIP-98 signature from exactly this key.
LUKE_MASTER_NPUB=
# Purely cosmetic — shown on Luke's card as "answers to …".
MASTER_NIP05=jaf@dequalsf.com

# --- Telegram approval channel -----------------------------------------
# Luke DMs you each draft with Approve/Reject buttons; on Approve the
# signer (above keys) signs + broadcasts. Create the bot with @BotFather.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# Your numeric Telegram user ID — the ONLY account whose taps are honored
# (message @userinfobot to get it). Not secret, but kept together.
TELEGRAM_APPROVER_ID=
# Secret token Telegram echoes back on every webhook call, so the box can
# reject forged updates. Any random string; set it at setWebhook time.
#   openssl rand -hex 24
TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# --- The propose bridge: brain → box -----------------------------------
# Bearer token the drafting brain (the scheduled Claude routine) presents
# on POST /propose. Only holders can queue a draft to your Telegram; posting
# still needs your tap. Any random string, shared with the routine.
#   openssl rand -hex 24
PROPOSE_TOKEN=

# --- OpenClaw / Hostinger cockpit sign-in ------------------------------
# The gateway auth token OpenClaw's Control UI expects on the box (:57419),
# if Luke's gate needs to present one. The "sign-in code from the box."
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=

# --- The brain: scheduled drafting (luke-brain.mjs) --------------------
# The brain calls the Anthropic API to draft posts from the day's signals.
# Reuse the same key the Director uses. 🔒
# Phase 2: Nactor loads this into memory (bootstrap-env) and BROKERS the call,
# so the brain need not read it directly once the broker path is on (below).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# --- Credential broker (Phase 2) — route LLM calls THROUGH Nactor ------
# If both are set, the brain sends Anthropic calls to Nactor's broker (which
# injects the key from memory) instead of hitting api.anthropic.com directly.
# Leave unset for the direct path. See nact/docs/migration.md.
#   NACT_BROKER_URL=http://nactor:8791/api        # Nactor on the compose network
# BRAIN_NSEC: a DEDICATED, activated `brain` identity used ONLY to sign the
# NIP-98 auth to the broker — NOT a posting key (can't post as luke/nave).
# GENERATE ON THE BOX like the other role keys; activate it once in the Nact app.
#   BRAIN_NSEC=
# Optional brain tuning (sensible defaults — leave unset to accept them):
# DRAFT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5
# PROPOSE_URL=https://luke.nave.pub/propose
# SUBSTACK_FEED=https://jafairweather.substack.com/feed
# NAVE_REPOS=nave.pub,noir,ntrigue,nvoy,nontact,nvelope,nherit,notegate,nostr-scoped-data-grants,luke
# SINCE_HOURS=14      # lookback window per run (a bit over the 12h half-cycle)
# MAX_POSTS=3

# --- Relays Luke broadcasts approved posts to --------------------------
LUKE_RELAYS=wss://relay.damus.io,wss://nos.lol,wss://relay.primal.net

# --- What you've delegated (shown on Luke's public card) ---------------
LUKE_MANDATE=To keep the master's work moving between visits.
LUKE_NAME=Luke

# --- Session cookie signing --------------------------------------------
# Optional. If unset, it's derived from LUKE_NSEC (so sessions survive
# restarts). Set a random value to rotate all sessions at once.
# GATE_SECRET=
# Cookie lifetime in seconds (default 12h).
# GATE_SESSION_TTL=43200

# --- Port (internal; Caddy is the public face) -------------------------
LUKE_PORT=8790
